In this article, President Biden expresses his concern about the high threat of a Russian invasion in Ukraine. He states that Russia has not moved any troops out and has even brought in more troops. He believes that Russia is engaged in a false-flag operation to justify an attack on Ukraine. The President mentions that he has been waiting for a response from Putin regarding his letter, which has been sent to the Moscow embassy. He has not read the response yet and cannot comment on it. President Biden's sense is that the invasion will happen within the next several days. He acknowledges that there is still a diplomatic path available and mentions Secretary Blinken's statement at the United Nations. The President has also laid out a path to Putin, but he does not have plans to call him at the moment.